rtant; transform: none !important; transform-origin: 400px 16.5px !important; zoom: 1 !important;"><lt-div class="lt-highlighter__scroll-element" style="top: 0px !important; left: 0px !important; width: 800px !important; height: 33px !important;"></lt-div></lt-div></lt-highlighter><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc="" data-lt-tmp-id="lt-33083" spellcheck="false" data-gramm="false"><h4 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><font color="#000000"><span style="caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Intra-abdominal Pressure&nbsp;</span></font></h4></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1666099744515" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1666099744515"><lt-highlighter contenteditable="false" style="display: none; z-index: auto !important;"><lt-div spellcheck="false" class="lt-highlighter__wrapper" style="width: 800px !important; height: 96px !important; transform: none !important; transform-origin: 400px 48px !important; zoom: 1 !important;"><lt-div class="lt-highlighter__scroll-element" style="top: 0px !important; left: 0px !important; width: 800px !important; height: 96px !important;"><canvas class="lt-highlighter__canvas" width="296" height="57" style="display: none; top: 4px !important; left: 302px !important;"></canvas></lt-div></lt-div></lt-highlighter><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc="" data-lt-tmp-id="lt-976955" spellcheck="false" data-gramm="false"><p>As I've discussed above, wearing a belt increases your ability to recruit your core musculature, creating much more intra-abdominal pressure vs just naturally bracing your core when not using a belt.</p><p>When deadlifting, you want to transfer as much force as possible from the ground up to your upper body whilst maintaining a neutral spine.</p><p><strong>By not using a belt for sub-maximal lifts, you learn how to naturally brace properly which then helps to get the most out of the belt when you wear it for maximal lifts.&nbsp;</strong></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1666099738486" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1666099738486"><lt-highlighter contenteditable="false" style="display: none; z-index: auto !important;"><lt-div spellcheck="false" class="lt-highlighter__wrapper" style="width: 800px !important; height: 33px !important; transform: none !important; transform-origin: 400px 16.5px !important; zoom: 1 !important;"><lt-div class="lt-highlighter__scroll-element" style="top: 0px !important; left: 0px !important; width: 800px !important; height: 33px !important;"></lt-div></lt-div></lt-highlighter><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc="" data-lt-tmp-id="lt-33083" spellcheck="false" data-gramm="false"><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><font color="#000000"><span style="caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Technique&nbsp;</span></font></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1666099744127" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1666099744127"><lt-highlighter contenteditable="false" style="display: none; z-index: auto !important;"><lt-div spellcheck="false" class="lt-highlighter__wrapper" style="width: 800px !important; height: 96px !important; transform: none !important; transform-origin: 400px 48px !important; zoom: 1 !important;"><lt-div class="lt-highlighter__scroll-element" style="top: 0px !important; left: 0px !important; width: 800px !important; height: 96px !important;"><canvas class="lt-highlighter__canvas" width="296" height="57" style="display: none; top: 4px !important; left: 302px !important;"></canvas></lt-div></lt-div>